        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: inbound metadata leakage — missing sentinels and display gaps",
        "body": "Closes #93966\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n\nInjected inbound metadata (sender info, conversation context) was not being stripped from user-visible chat messages, leaking internal routing metadata to end users.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nAdded `stripInboundMetadata` and `hasInboundMetadataSentinel` functions that detect and strip the inbound metadata sentinel block from chat text before it reaches the user.\n\n## Evidence\n\n```text\n$ npx tsx -e 'import { stripInboundMetadata, hasInboundMetadataSentinel } from \"./src/auto-reply/reply/strip-inbound-meta.ts\"; ...'\n\nWith metadata:\n  hasInboundMetadataSentinel: true\n  stripped: Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\nHello, how can I help you?\n\nWithout metadata:\n  hasInboundMetadataSentinel: false\n  unchanged: Hello, how can I help you?\n```\n\nThe metadata sentinel is detected and stripped. Ordinary user text without metadata is unchanged (no false positives).",
